'''Beryl Baxter''' (born 8 April 1926) is a British film actress whose career spanned from the 1940s to the 1970s.<ref name="IMDB">[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0062685 Profile], imdb.com; accessed 10 October 2014.</ref>

==Early and personal life==
'''Beryl Ivory''' was born in [[Birmingham]], [[England]] on 8 April 1926. Adopting the stage name Beryl Baxter, she supported hopes of becoming the new [[Margaret Lockwood]].<ref name="Britmovie">[http://www.britmovie.co.uk/forums/actors-actresses/104552-beryl-baxter.html Profile] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923221509/http://www.britmovie.co.uk/forums/actors-actresses/104552-beryl-baxter.html |date=2015-09-23 }}, Britmovie.com; accessed 10 October 2014.</ref> She made her film debut in 1948 as a leading role in [[The Idol of Paris]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bfi.org.uk/films-tv-people/4ce2b9f72bfd1|title=Beryl Baxter|website=BFI}}</ref> She married Bernard Gross in 1952.<ref name="Britmovie"/>

==Filmography==
* ''[[The Idol of Paris]]'' – Theresa (1948)
* ''Sherlock Holmes: The Man Who Disappeared'' – Doreen (1951)
* ''[[Counterspy (film)|Counterspy]]'' – (uncredited; 1953)
* ''The Mayerling Affair'' – Princess Stephanie (1956)
* ''[[Encounter (1958 TV series)|Encounter (TV series)]]'' – Pamela Brooks (one episode: "Depth 300"; 1958)
* ''Charles Tupper: The Big Man'' – (1961)
* ''[[The Avengers (TV series)|The Avengers]]'' (TV series) – Helen Rayner (one episode: "[[The Outside-In Man]]"; 1964)
* ''[[The Protectors]]''  – Miss. Nicholson (one episode: "The Stamp Collection"; 1964)
* ''[[Undermind (TV series)|Undermind]]'' (TV series) – Veronica (one episode: "End Signal"; 1965)
* ''[[Love Story (UK TV series)|Love Story]]'' (TV series) – Ivy Burns (one episode: "The Sad Smile of the Mona Lisa"; 1965) 
* ''[[Thirteen Against Fate]]'' –  Madame Fabien (one episode, entitled 'The Son') (1966)
* ''Detective'' (TV Series) – Mrs. Stephenson (one episode, entitled 'The Public School Murder') (1969)
* ''Crime of Passion'' (TV series) – Mme. Juhan (episode: "Magdalena"; 1971)

